68X509_REQ *X509_to_X509_REQ(X509 *x, EVP_PKEY *pkey, const EVP_MD *md)
69{
70 X509_REQ *ret;
71 X509_REQ_INFO *ri;
72 int i;
73 EVP_PKEY *pktmp;
74
75 ret = X509_REQ_new();
76 if (ret == NULL) {
77 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
78 goto err;
79 }
80
81 ri = ret->req_info;
82
83 ri->version->length = 1;
84 ri->version->data = (unsigned char *)OPENSSL_malloc(1);
85 if (ri->version->data == NULL)
86 goto err;
87 ri->version->data[0] = 0; /* version == 0 */
88
89 if (!X509_REQ_set_subject_name(ret, X509_get_subject_name(x)))
90 goto err;
91
92 pktmp = X509_get_pubkey(x);
93 if (pktmp == NULL)
94 goto err;
95 i = X509_REQ_set_pubkey(ret, pktmp);
96 EVP_PKEY_free(pktmp);
97 if (!i)
98 goto err;
99
100 if (pkey != NULL) {
101 if (!X509_REQ_sign(ret, pkey, md))
102 goto err;
103 }
104 return (ret);
105 err:
106 X509_REQ_free(ret);
107 return (NULL);
108}
109
110long X509_REQ_get_version(const X509_REQ *req)
111{
112 return ASN1_INTEGER_get(req->req_info->version);
113}
114
115X509_NAME *X509_REQ_get_subject_name(const X509_REQ *req)
116{
117 return req->req_info->subject;
118}
119
120EVP_PKEY *X509_REQ_get_pubkey(X509_REQ *req)
121{
122 if ((req == NULL) || (req->req_info == NULL))
123 return (NULL);
124 return (X509_PUBKEY_get(req->req_info->pubkey));
125}
126
127int X509_REQ_check_private_key(X509_REQ *x, EVP_PKEY *k)
128{
129 EVP_PKEY *xk = NULL;
130 int ok = 0;
131
132 xk = X509_REQ_get_pubkey(x);
133 switch (EVP_PKEY_cmp(xk, k)) {
134 case 1:
135 ok = 1;
136 break;
137 case 0:
138 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, X509_R_KEY_VALUES_MISMATCH);
139 break;
140 case -1:
141 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, X509_R_KEY_TYPE_MISMATCH);
142 break;
143 case -2:
144 if (k->type == EVP_PKEY_EC) {
145 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, ERR_R_EC_LIB);
146 break;
147 }
148 if (k->type == EVP_PKEY_DH) {
149 /* No idea */
150 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, X509_R_CANT_CHECK_DH_KEY);
151 break;
152 }
153 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, X509_R_UNKNOWN_KEY_TYPE);
154 }
155
156 EVP_PKEY_free(xk);
157 return (ok);
158}

160int X509_REQ_extension_nid(int req_nid)
161{
162 return req_nid == NID_ext_req || req_nid == NID_ms_ext_req;
163}
164
165STACK_OF(X509_EXTENSION) *X509_REQ_get_extensions(X509_REQ *req)
166{
167 if (req == NULL || req->req_info == NULL) {
168 return NULL;
169 }
170
171 int idx = X509_REQ_get_attr_by_NID(req, NID_ext_req, -1);
172 if (idx == -1) {
173 idx = X509_REQ_get_attr_by_NID(req, NID_ms_ext_req, -1);
174 }
175 if (idx == -1) {
176 return NULL;
177 }
178
179 X509_ATTRIBUTE *attr = X509_REQ_get_attr(req, idx);
180 ASN1_TYPE *ext = X509_ATTRIBUTE_get0_type(attr, 0);
181 if (!ext || ext->type != V_ASN1_SEQUENCE) {
182 return NULL;
183 }
184 const unsigned char *p = ext->value.sequence->data;
185 return (STACK_OF(X509_EXTENSION) *)
186 ASN1_item_d2i(NULL, &p, ext->value.sequence->length,
187 ASN1_ITEM_rptr(X509_EXTENSIONS));
188}
189
190/*
191 * Add a STACK_OF extensions to a certificate request: allow alternative OIDs
192 * in case we want to create a non standard one.
193 */
194
195int X509_REQ_add_extensions_nid(X509_REQ *req,
196 const STACK_OF(X509_EXTENSION) *exts, int nid)
197{
198 /* Generate encoding of extensions */
199 unsigned char *ext = NULL;
200 int ext_len = ASN1_item_i2d((ASN1_VALUE *)exts, &ext,
201 ASN1_ITEM_rptr(X509_EXTENSIONS));
202 if (ext_len <= 0) {
203 return 0;
204 }
205 int ret = X509_REQ_add1_attr_by_NID(req, nid, V_ASN1_SEQUENCE, ext,
206 ext_len);
207 OPENSSL_free(ext);
208 return ret;
209}
210
211/* This is the normal usage: use the "official" OID */
212int X509_REQ_add_extensions(X509_REQ *req,
213 const STACK_OF(X509_EXTENSION) *exts)
214{
215 return X509_REQ_add_extensions_nid(req, exts, NID_ext_req);
216}

246int X509_REQ_add1_attr(X509_REQ *req, X509_ATTRIBUTE *attr)
247{

249 return 1;
250 return 0;
251}

283void X509_REQ_get0_signature(const X509_REQ *req, const ASN1_BIT_STRING **psig,
284 const X509_ALGOR **palg)
285{
286 if (psig != NULL)
287 *psig = req->signature;
288 if (palg != NULL)
289 *palg = req->sig_alg;
290}
291
292int X509_REQ_get_signature_nid(const X509_REQ *req)
293{
294 return OBJ_obj2nid(req->sig_alg->algorithm);
295}
296
297int i2d_re_X509_REQ_tbs(X509_REQ *req, unsigned char **pp)
298{
299 req->req_info->enc.modified = 1;
300 return i2d_X509_REQ_INFO(req->req_info, pp);
301}
